<item>
            <title>[LU-17328] don&apos;t allow non-ASCII characters in commit messages</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17328</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Some Git commit messages have control characters, or fancy quotation marks or mdash hyphens or similar, and this messes up the display of &quot;&lt;tt&gt;git log&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; and other tools.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Add a check into &lt;tt&gt;commit-msg&lt;/tt&gt; to reject commit messages that have non-ASCII characters.  This does not apply to characters used in &lt;tt&gt;Signed-off-by:&lt;/tt&gt; or similar fields that may contain people&apos;s names.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
